    "title": "ldconfig does not update the library cache on make install",
    "body": "I see that a call to `ldconfig -n /usr/local/lib` happens during `make install`, but that doesn't cause the shared library cache to be updated as `-n` implies `-N` (which instructs ldconfig to not rebuild the cache):\n\n```\n$ sudo ldconfig -n /usr/local/lib\n$ ldconfig -p | grep secp\n$ sudo ldconfig /usr/local/lib\n$ ldconfig -p | grep secp\n    libsecp256k1.so.0 (libc6,x86-64) => /usr/local/lib/libsecp256k1.so.0\n    libsecp256k1.so (libc6,x86-64) => /usr/local/lib/libsecp256k1.so\n```\n",
